# `go build ./gw/cmd/gwag` from the repo root drops a `gwag` binary
# here. Use `bin/gwag` (cached under bin/.run/) instead.
/gwag

# `gwag login` / `gwag up` write a project-local context directory
# containing credentials.json (with admin bearer tokens) and per-
# context runtime state (JetStream, admin-token persistence). Never
# commit it.
.gw/

# Maintainer working documents; not adopter-facing material.
/docs/plan.md
/docs/todo.md
/docs/api-audit.md
/docs/codegen-spike.md
